Definition.WordDefinition: Cash \Cash\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Cashed}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Casing}.] To pay, or to receive, cash for; to exchange for money; as, cash a note or an order. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: cashed \cashed\ adj. converted into currency; -- of financial instruments; as, a cashed check. [WordNet 1.5]
cashed adj : for which money has been paid; "a cashed check"
